### ================================================================
### CIVICREPORT — EXTENSIVE API TEST FILE
### All 3 Workflows — Multiple Records — Full WF3 Coverage
### ================================================================
### Extension: REST Client by Huachao Mao (VS Code)
###
### INSTRUCTIONS:
###   1. Start server: node server.js
###   2. Run Section 0 first (setup tokens)
###   3. Paste tokens at top after login
###   4. Run Sections 1-2 to seed data (multiple issues + upvotes)
###   5. Run Section 3 (admin status updates — needed for WF3 resolution time)
###   6. Run Section 4 (full WF3 analytics tests)
###   7. Run Section 5 (full WF3 reports CRUD tests)
###   8. Run Section 6 (edge cases + error handling)
### ================================================================

@baseUrl       = http://localhost:5001
@citizenToken  = PASTE_CITIZEN_TOKEN_HERE
@citizen2Token = PASTE_CITIZEN2_TOKEN_HERE
@adminToken    = PASTE_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE
@issueId1      = PASTE_ISSUE_ID_1
@issueId2      = PASTE_ISSUE_ID_2
@issueId3      = PASTE_ISSUE_ID_3
@issueId4      = PASTE_ISSUE_ID_4
@issueId5      = PASTE_ISSUE_ID_5
@issueId6      = PASTE_ISSUE_ID_6
@reportId      = PASTE_REPORT_ID_HERE


### ================================================================
### SECTION 0 — SETUP: Register & Login (run these first)
### ================================================================

### [0.1] Register Citizen 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "phone": "+923001234567",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe"
}

###

### [0.2] Register Citizen 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "sara@example.com",
  "phone": "+923009876543",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "Sara",
  "lastName": "Khan"
}

###

### [0.3] Login Citizen 1 with EMAIL → copy token → paste into @citizenToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### [0.4] Login Citizen 1 with PHONE → should also return 200 (Fix 1 test)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone": "+923001234567",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### [0.5] Login Citizen 2 → copy token → paste into @citizen2Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "sara@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### [0.6] Register Admin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@civicreport.com",
  "password": "admin123",
  "name": "City Admin"
}

###

### [0.7] Login Admin → copy token → paste into @adminToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@civicreport.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###

### [0.8] Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/health

