### ================================================================
### SECTION 1 — SEED: Report 6 Issues (different categories & areas)
### Copy each returned `id` into the @issueId variables at the top
### ================================================================

### [1.1] Issue 1 — Garbage / Downtown
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/issues
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Overflowing garbage bins on Main Street",
  "description": "Three bins near the bus stop have been overflowing for 5 days. Smell is unbearable.",
  "category": "Garbage",
  "latitude": 24.8607,
  "longitude": 67.0011,
  "address": "Main Street, Downtown"
}

###

### [1.2] Issue 2 — Garbage / Sector 4
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/issues
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Illegal dumping near park",
  "description": "Large pile of construction waste dumped near children's park entrance",
  "category": "Garbage",
  "latitude": 24.8750,
  "longitude": 67.0150,
  "address": "Sector 4, North Block"
}

###

### [1.3] Issue 3 — Road / Downtown
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/issues
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Large pothole causing accidents",
  "description": "Deep pothole on main road near traffic signal. Two motorcycles fell this week.",
  "category": "Road",
  "latitude": 24.8620,
  "longitude": 67.0025,
  "address": "Main Street, Downtown"
}

###

### [1.4] Issue 4 — Water / Sector 4
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/issues
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Water supply cut for 3 days",
  "description": "Entire block has no water supply since Monday. No notice given by authority.",
  "category": "Water",
  "latitude": 24.8760,
  "longitude": 67.0160,
  "address": "Sector 4, North Block"
}

###

### [1.5] Issue 5 — Electricity / Zone B
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/issues
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Street lights not working",
  "description": "All street lights on the boulevard have been off for 2 weeks. Very unsafe at night.",
  "category": "Electricity",
  "latitude": 24.8690,
  "longitude": 67.0080,
  "address": "Zone B, Industrial Area"
}

###

### [1.6] Issue 6 — Road / Zone B (reported by Citizen 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/issues
Authorization: Bearer {{citizen2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Bridge railing completely broken",
  "description": "The safety railing on the pedestrian bridge is broken. Dangerous for children.",
  "category": "Road",
  "latitude": 24.8700,
  "longitude": 67.0090,
  "address": "Zone B, Industrial Area"
}

###


### ================================================================
### SECTION 2 — SEED: Upvotes (multiple users upvoting multiple issues)
### This seeds upvoteCount data which WF3 analytics uses
### ================================================================

### [2.1] Citizen 1 upvotes Issue 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upvotes
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "issueId": "{{issueId2}}" }

###

### [2.2] Citizen 1 upvotes Issue 3
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upvotes
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "issueId": "{{issueId3}}" }

###

### [2.3] Citizen 1 upvotes Issue 5
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upvotes
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "issueId": "{{issueId5}}" }

###

### [2.4] Citizen 2 upvotes Issue 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upvotes
Authorization: Bearer {{citizen2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "issueId": "{{issueId1}}" }

###

### [2.5] Citizen 2 upvotes Issue 3
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upvotes
Authorization: Bearer {{citizen2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "issueId": "{{issueId3}}" }

###

### [2.6] Citizen 2 upvotes Issue 4
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/upvotes
Authorization: Bearer {{citizen2Token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "issueId": "{{issueId4}}" }

###

### [2.7] Verify — Issue 3 should have upvoteCount = 2 (highest priority)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues/{{issueId3}}

###

### [2.8] Get all issues sorted by priority — Issue 3 should be first
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?sortBy=upvoteCount

###

### [2.9] Filter issues by area — should return issues 1 and 3 only
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?area=Downtown

###

### [2.10] Filter by category
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?category=Garbage

###


### ================================================================
### SECTION 3 — ADMIN: Status Updates
### CRITICAL for WF3 — resolution time analytics needs resolved issues
### ================================================================

### [3.1] Admin views all issues
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### [3.2] Admin sorts by priority (upvoteCount)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues?sortBy=upvoteCount
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### [3.3] Admin filters by area
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues?area=Downtown
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### [3.4] Admin filters by category + area
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues?category=Garbage&area=Sector+4
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### [3.5] Admin filters by date range
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues?dateFrom=2026-01-01&dateTo=2026-12-31
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### [3.6] Admin views Issue 1 full detail (image, upvotes, status logs)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### [3.7] Move Issue 1: Pending → In Progress
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "In Progress",
  "remarks": "Assigned to municipal waste team. Collection scheduled for tomorrow."
}

###

### [3.8] Move Issue 1: In Progress → Resolved
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "Resolved",
  "remarks": "Garbage cleared and bins relocated. Issue fully resolved."
}

###

### [3.9] Move Issue 2: Pending → In Progress
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "In Progress",
  "remarks": "Waste removal team dispatched to Sector 4."
}

###

### [3.10] Move Issue 2: In Progress → Resolved
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "Resolved",
  "remarks": "Construction waste removed. Area cleaned."
}

###

### [3.11] Move Issue 3: Pending → In Progress
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId3}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "In Progress",
  "remarks": "Road repair crew scheduled for this week."
}

###

### [3.12] Move Issue 3: In Progress → Resolved
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId3}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "Resolved",
  "remarks": "Pothole filled and road surface repaired."
}

###

### [3.13] Move Issue 5: Pending → Rejected
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId5}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "Rejected",
  "remarks": "This area falls under private company jurisdiction, not municipal authority."
}

###

### [3.14] Issue 4 stays In Progress, Issue 6 stays Pending
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues/{{issueId4}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "newStatus": "In Progress",
  "remarks": "Water supply team investigating the pipeline break."
}

###

### [3.15] Verify notifications fired — admin gets notified
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### [3.16] Get status log history for Issue 1 (should show 2 entries)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/status-logs/issue/{{issueId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###

### [3.17] Get status log history for Issue 3 (should show 2 entries)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/status-logs/issue/{{issueId3}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

###


### ================================================================
### SECTION 4 — WORKFLOW 3: ANALYTICS (Extensive)
### Run AFTER Section 3 so resolved issues exist for resolution time
### ================================================================

# ── 4A. Overview Stats ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### [4.1] Overview — all issues, no filter
### Expected: totalIssues=6, byStatus has Pending/InProgress/Resolved/Rejected, totalUpvotes=6
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/overview

###

### [4.2] Overview — filter by status=Resolved
### Expected: totalIssues=3 (issues 1,2,3), totalUpvotes reflects only resolved ones
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/overview?status=Resolved

###

### [4.3] Overview — filter by category=Garbage
### Expected: totalIssues=2 (issues 1,2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/overview?category=Garbage

###

### [4.4] Overview — filter by area=Downtown
### Expected: totalIssues=2 (issues 1,3)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/overview?area=Downtown

###

### [4.5] Overview — filter by date range (today)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/overview?dateFrom=2026-04-01&dateTo=2026-12-31

###

### [4.6] Overview — combined filters: category + area
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/analytics/overview?category=Road&area=Downtown

###

