### SECTION 5 — WORKFLOW 3: REPORTS CRUD (Extensive)
### ================================================================

# ── 5A. CREATE Reports ────────────────────────────────────────────

### [5.1] Create Report 1 — all issues, no filters
### Copy the returned `id` → paste into @reportId at the top
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reports
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Full System Snapshot — All Issues",
  "filters": {}
}

###

### [5.2] Create Report 2 — Garbage category only
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reports
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Garbage Issues Report",
  "filters": {
    "category": "Garbage"
  }
}

###

### [5.3] Create Report 3 — Resolved issues only
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reports
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Resolved Issues — Q2 2026",
  "filters": {
    "status": "Resolved",
    "dateFrom": "2026-04-01",
    "dateTo": "2026-06-30"
  }
}

###

### [5.4] Create Report 4 — Downtown area
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reports
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Downtown Area Issues",
  "filters": {
    "area": "Downtown"
  }
}

###

### [5.5] Create Report — missing title → should return 400
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reports
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "filters": { "category": "Road" }
}

###

### [5.6] Create Report — no token → should return 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/reports
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Unauthorized Report",
  "filters": {}
}

###

