### ================================================================
### SECTION 7 — LOCATION DENSITY PRIORITY SCORE
### Run AFTER Section 1 (issues seeded) and Section 2 (upvotes seeded)
### Issues 1 and 3 are both in "Downtown" close coordinates — they
### should boost each other's nearbyIssueCount and priorityScore
### ================================================================

### [7.1] Get issues sorted by PRIORITY (upvotes + location density)
### Expected: each issue has priorityScore and nearbyIssueCount fields
### Issue 3 (2 upvotes + nearby Issue 1) should rank higher than
### Issue 1 (1 upvote + nearby Issue 3)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?sortBy=priority

###

### [7.2] Compare — same issues sorted by upvoteCount only
### Notice the order may differ from priority sort above
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?sortBy=upvoteCount

###

### [7.3] Compare — default sort (newest first, no priority)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues

###

### [7.4] Priority sort + category filter
### Expected: only Garbage issues, sorted by priorityScore
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?sortBy=priority&category=Garbage

###

### [7.5] Priority sort + area filter
### Expected: only Downtown issues (1 and 3), both have nearbyIssueCount=1
### priorityScore = upvoteCount + (1 × 2) for each
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?sortBy=priority&area=Downtown

###

### [7.6] Priority sort + status filter
### Expected: only Pending issues sorted by score
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?sortBy=priority&status=Pending

###

### [7.7] Verify priorityScore values make sense
### Issue 1: 1 upvote + 1 nearby = 1 + (1×2) = 3
### Issue 3: 2 upvotes + 1 nearby = 2 + (1×2) = 4  ← should rank first
### Issue 2: 1 upvote + 0 nearby = 1 + (0×2) = 1
### Issue 4: 1 upvote + 0 nearby = 1
### Issue 5: 1 upvote + 1 nearby (Issue 6 also Zone B) = 1 + 2 = 3
### Issue 6: 0 upvotes + 1 nearby = 0 + 2 = 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/issues?sortBy=priority

###

### [7.8] Admin also sees priority sort
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/admin/issues?sortBy=upvoteCount
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

